us dissident groupings and their tactics within a post-Good Friday Agreement context and places armed republicanism in Northern Ireland within the broader debate on counter-terrorism after 9/11.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh  aGood Friday Agreement.  aIRA.  aIrish republicanism.  aNorthern Ireland.  aSinn Féin.  acounter-terrorism.  adissidents.  apeace process.  apolitical violence.  aterrorism.1 aWhiting, Sophie A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909869740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719098697423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719098697/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles